# MCP Policy

This file defines how Chrome DevTools MCP should be used in this workspace.

## Default Rule

- Do not use Chrome MCP unless explicitly requested in the chat.
- Prefer code/file analysis first.
- If MCP is needed, start with read-only actions.

## Approval Model

- Read-only actions: allowed by default once MCP is explicitly enabled.
- Mutating actions: require explicit approval in the same chat.
- Sensitive actions (file upload, destructive clicks, non-localhost navigation): require explicit approval each time.

## Allowed Scopes

- Allowed hosts by default:
  - `localhost`
  - `127.0.0.1`
- Any other domain requires explicit approval.

