## Workflow Profiles

### Profile A: Read-only Audit

Use when validating UI state without changing anything.

- Allowed: read-only tools only.
- No clicks, no typing, no navigation changes.

### Profile B: Local Interaction Test

Use for local QA flows on localhost.

- Allowed hosts: localhost and 127.0.0.1 only.
- Allowed: read-only + basic interactions (`click`, `fill`, `press_key`).
- Blocked unless approved: file upload, memory/perf tracing.

### Profile C: Full E2E Debug

Use for deep troubleshooting.

- Allowed: all tools.
- Require explicit task scope before starting.
- Capture only the minimum artifacts needed.

## Required Confirmation Format

Before using mutating tools, confirm with one line:

- `MCP plan: [goal] | tools: [list] | target: [url/host]`

Proceed only after user approval.

## Prompt Snippets

Use these at the top of a chat.

### Strict mode

- Follow MCP_POLICY strictly.
- Do not use MCP unless I say "use MCP".
- If I allow MCP, read-only only unless I approve mutating actions.

### Local QA mode

- Follow MCP_POLICY Profile B.
- Restrict all MCP actions to localhost/127.0.0.1.
- Ask before using advanced diagnostics.

## Notes

- This policy is guidance for agent behavior.
- Hard enforcement should be implemented with client-side tool restrictions or an MCP proxy.
